node_modules

# Runtime state lives in `.ouro/`, but do NOT blanket-ignore it here. The
# directory carries its own `.ouro/.gitignore` (written by `ouro init`) using an
# ignore-everything-then-unignore-safe pattern: it keeps run/, logs/,
# worktrees/, .env and tickets.json out while committing agents/, context/ and
# config.json — those are the point. A `.ouro` line at this level would defeat
# that nested file entirely: git never re-includes a path under a parent that a
# higher .gitignore already excluded, so the un-ignore rules would never apply.

# Build output. `npm run bundle` regenerates both, and the cli package rebuilds
# dashboard-dist in prepublishOnly before it goes to npm, so neither belongs in
# git. A fresh clone runs `npm run bundle` — see Setup in the README.
packages/dashboard/dist
packages/cli/dashboard-dist
.dist
